<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<bibRefCitation author="Ausserer, A" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft (Wien)" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="125 - 206" title="Zweiter Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Arachniden-Familie der Territelariae Thorell (Mygalidae Autor)." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/16420158page/229/mode/1up" volume="25" year="1875">Ausserer (1875)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned several females from Cuba and two specimens from &quot;Santa 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fé">Fe</normalizedToken>
de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bogotá”">Bogota&quot;</normalizedToken>
(known, nowadays, as Bogota, capital of Colombia) in Keyserling collection (housed at the BMNH). All examined specimens from Cuba have urticating setae type III on abdomen dorsum, and all specimens from Bogota have setae type I. Therefore, they belong to subfamily 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Theraphosinae">Theraphosinae</taxonomicName>
and it is, herein, removed from the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Avicularia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Avicularia" order="Araneae" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Avicularia</taxonomicName>
. All syntypes are immatures lacking diagnostic characters and, therefore, we consider 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Ischnocolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ischnocolus hirsutum" order="Araneae" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutum">Ischnocolus hirsutum</taxonomicName>
Ausserer, 1875 a nomen dubium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
